1. Press the <ESC> key (to make sure you are in Normal mode).

2. Type:      :q! <ENTER>.
     This exits the editor, DISCARDING any changes you have made.
     
x key to delete 

h - left 
j - down
k - up
l - left 

i - insert text at the cursor

shift + a - append text at the end of the line

:wq - save file and exit 

vim nameOfTheFile - is the command to start vim editor, nameOfTheFile is the name of the file you wish to edit

dw - delete a word 
d$ - delete to the end of the line 
de - delete to the end of the current word 
dNw - where N is the number of words that you want to delete
dd - delete a whole line
Ndd - where N is a number. Deletes multiple lines

w - move cursor one word to the right. Typing a number before a motion repeats it N times. 2w - move two words. 
0 - move cursor to the begging of the line

u - undo the last command

p - paste previously deleted line 

rN - replace, N is the character we want to replace with 
